         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>404</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>122</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>321f</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1970"/><citedRange>261</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5 #a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1968"/><citedRange>224</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1979b"/><citedRange>36</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">How will the antarakalpa of illness come here? … then because of that illness [the] people die.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>668</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6 #a7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1970"/><citedRange>262</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">How will the antarakalpa of hunger come here? Then because of that hunger the three continents starve within seven days …</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>669</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">"(Wie kommt dann der Antara)kalpa des Hungers?" [Antwort:] "Die drei Kontinente verhungern dann durch den Hunger (innerhalb von) sieben Tagen."</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">"(How, then, does the Antara)kalpa of hunger (arrive)?" [Answer:] "The three continents then will starve through the hunger (within) seven days."</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>111</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8 #b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">How will the … of the śastrakalpa come, then? … it will enter … day …</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>669</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>255f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">How will these beings be seen by each other? Terrible mind …</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>669</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Wie werden die Wesen voneinander(?) gesehen? oder: Wie zeigen sich [d.h. verhalten sich(?)] die Wesen zueinander(?) ?</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">How are the beings seen by each other(?) ? OR: How do the beings show themselves [i.e. behave(?)] towards each other(?) ?</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>255-6</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Es entsteht [wtl. erhebt sich] das Verlangen sich gegenseitig zu töten.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The desire to kill each other arises.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>283</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... zum (Töt)en gebrauchte er [sein] (Schwert) ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... for (kill)ing he used [his] (sword) ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>407</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
